result.execSummary:
The defendant Jay H Zeinert was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jay H Zeinert in court, in custody.  Catharine Denise White appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  DA makes her recommendation.  Court orders 30 days jail each count concurrently w/Huber. $100+costs on each count.  Appeal rights.

Defendant appears before Judge Habeck regarding this case as well as other matters and agrees that he can handle all matters.  DA indicates her recommendations to a global resolution of defendant's cases.  Defendant enters a plea of no contest to Counts 1 & 3.  Court advises party of their rights, finds factual basis, accepts defendant's waiver of their rights, the plea made, and finds guilty. Count 2 DRI.  Sentencing set for a later date as victim in other matter wants to be present.  Bond continued.

Defendant Jay H Zeinert in court, in custody.  Scott E. Niemi appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Right to counsel given - defendant proceeds w/o counsel.  Court accepts waiver of attorney for now.  Defendant enters a plea of not guilty.  Bond continued.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for May 3, 2016 at 03:45 pm.

Absolute sobriety.  No illegal substances.  Only prescription medication with a valid prescription.  No class B licensed establishments.  
Picture and Prints.

Defendant Jay H Zeinert appeared by video means. Prosecuting Atty Scott E. Niemi appeared for State of Wisconsin.  Right to an attorney given.  He wants to represent himself.  Judge agrees for now that he can.  No plea entered today would like some time to consider his plea options.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for April 25, 2016 at 01:30 pm.
